text: A Tequeño is a type of fried cheese that is breaded. The cheese is usually queso blanco (white cheese). It came from the Venezuelan town of Los Teques. It is popular in Venezuela as a snack for parties. ==Preparation== To prepare it, the dough is wrapped around a cheesestick and formed into a breadstick so it can be fried in oil for 6 minutes at or sometimes oven-baked. Other things can go inside the filling such as chocolate or chorizo. ==References== Category:Venezuelan food Category:Breads Category:Snack foods
title: Tequeño
